- A 'completed' event status indicates that the event has finished and the final scores are available;
- Home wins are determined when the home team's score is greater than the away team's score;
- Away wins are determined when the away team's score is greater than the home team's score.

- "Top performers" refers to teams with a performance rank of 3 or better within their league;
- "Performance rank" is based on the average score of the team across all matches;
- "Average score" is calculated as the sum of home and away scores divided by the number of matches.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS season_count_with_one_champion
FROM seasons
WHERE champion_team IS NOT NULL;

external_knowledge:
- "top 3 teams" refers to the teams ranked highest based on their average home scores;
- "average home scores" are calculated by averaging the scores of the home team across all seasons;
- "leagues" are the specific competitions in which the teams participate.

- Performance is based on the total number of wins and losses;
- Teams are ranked first by the total number of wins (higher wins rank higher) and then by the total number of losses (fewer losses rank higher);
- Average attendance is an additional metric used to evaluate team popularity, but it does not directly affect the ranking.

- "Above-average number of victories" refers to leagues where the average wins are greater than the overall average wins across all leagues;
- "Most popular venue" refers to the venue with the highest total attendance;
- "Drawing the largest crowds" refers to the venue with the highest total number of spectators.

- 'natural grass' refers to the type of playing surface;
- 'completed' indicates that the event has finished;
- 'home team' is the team playing at their home venue;
- 'average score of the home team' is the mean score of the home team across the selected events;
- 'total attendance' is the sum of all spectators for the selected events.

- "Top 3 performers" refers to the teams with the highest average scores in their respective leagues and seasons;
- "Overall average score" is the average score of a team across all its games in all leagues and seasons;
- "Average of all teams" is the mean of the overall average scores of all teams.

- 'Top 3 most attended events' refers to the events with the highest number of spectators;
- 'Home team won' means the home team's score is greater than the away team's score;
- 'Event was completed' means the event status is 'completed'.

- 'Completed events' refers to events where the event_status is 'completed';
- 'Score difference' is calculated as the score of the home team minus the score of the away team;
- 'Average score' is the average of the total scores (home + away) for all completed events in the same league.

- "Seasons" refer to specific periods during which sports events are held;
- "Venues" are the locations where events take place;
- "Leagues" are groups of teams that compete against each other;
- "Teams" are the groups of players competing in the events;
- "Events" are the matches or games that are held;
- "Users" are the individuals who interact with the system;
- "Logs" are records of user activity;
- "Average attendance" is the mean number of spectators at events;
- "Games per league" and "games per season" indicate the distribution of games across leagues and seasons, respectively;
- "Average score" is the mean total score of all events;
- "Away team win rate" is the percentage of times the away team wins an event.
